      "content": {
        "title": "Benign Soft Tissue Tumors — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Lipoma, pigmented villonodular synovitis, nerve sheath tumors, and other benign soft-tissue masses.",
        "summary": "PVNS may be diffuse or localized; synovectomy is treatment. Lipomas are common; atypical features warrant MRI. Schwannomas arise from nerve sheath."
      },
